	    <h3>The Wishlist</h3>
For all of the items on the wishlist we're sure it should be possible to build them into Hippo CMS given its broad architectural foundations. We simply have not yet had the change or the need to implement them. For some we already have a partial implementation, but it requires a little extra effort to turn them into reusable components.
<p>
Contact <a href="http://www.onehippo.com/en/support">Hippo Support</a> directly if you need any of the following features:</p>
		<ul>
		<li> Customizable help</li>
		<li> Personalized reporting ("My recent documents", "My Tasks", etc)</li>
		<li> DMS functionality</li>
		<li> External BPM layer</li>
		<li> Repository-wide content tagging and labeling</li>
		<li> Archiver (roll back to a specific date)</li>
		<li> Visitor generated metadata management</li>
		<li> Collection management</li>
		<li> Word import</li>
		<li> Split pane versioning</li>
		<li> Translations workflow</li>
		<li> Metadata / tag suggestors</li>
		<li> User profiles (different UI configurations for different user profiles)</li>
		<li> Knowledge driven workflow</li>
		<li> Website templating (Freemarker / JSP templates)</li>
		<li> Task management</li>
		<li> Search in pickers</li>
		<li> Upload in image picker</li>
		<li> Save draft</li>
		<li> Advanced Search</li>
		<li> Multi-upload</li>
		<li> Improved CMS plugin development</li>
		<li> Improved image management (tagging, collections, previews, thumbnails)</li>
		<li> Taxonomy picker and Taxonomy editor</li>
		<li> Form builder</li>
		<li> Versioning (Version management user interface, history browsing)</li>
		<li> Search in pickers</li>
		<li> Permissions management user interface for folders and domains</li>
		<li> Separated deployment</li>
		<li> Batch workflow actions on search results</li>
		<li> Forms management</li>
		<li> Extended metadata extraction (PDF, Word, Images, etc)</li>
		<li> REST interface</li>
		<li> CMIS interface</li>
		</ul>

